<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 27 at 5:32PM EDT until August 27 at 6:15PM EDT by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>The National Weather Service in Raleigh has issued a
* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Anson County in central North Carolina...
South central Richmond County in central North Carolina...
* Until 615 PM EDT.
* At 531 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 8 miles east of
Wadesboro, moving southwest at 5 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
* Locations impacted include...
Wadesboro, Lilesville, Morven, McFarlan and Diggs.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
